This paper deals with algorithms for maintaining a topological ordering of a directed acyclic graph (DAG), which is a fundamental problem in computer science. The paper presents an average-case analysis of online topological ordering algorithms, which suggests that it is likely to be categorized under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.AL (Computational Complexity and Algorithms). The paper also involves probabilistic analysis, which suggests that it could be categorized under cs.CC (Computational Complexity) or cs.LG (Machine Learning) as well. Finally, the paper deals with graphs and their properties, which suggests that it could be categorized under cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) as well.
